          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-18 08:38:27" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a Semitic idiom, literally: one who puts his hand to the plow and looks back) to begin some activity requiring close attention but then to change one’s mind about proceeding</DefinitionShort>
